Rating: 4
I used this recipe as a jumping off point and made several modifications. My toddler sometimes likes crispy kale, so I roasted the kale in the oven. I made the polenta in a double boiler so I wouldn't have to constantly stir and made it with water instead of milk. I fried up 3/4 lb of thick sliced bacon cut up in bite sized pieces. I poured off some of the rendered bacon fat, and sauteed a double portion of shiitake mushrooms with rosemary, thyme and onion in the remaining fat. When I was ready to serve, I stirred a heaping handful of grated sharp cheddar cheese into the polenta then toped it with the mushrooms and then the crispy kale and bacon bits.

Rating: 4
I loved this! The combination of flavors is outstanding. I did a few things differently: Instead of boiling the kale and then draining it, I sauteed it first with garlic and onion, added broth and let it cook until the liquid boiled off and it was a good texture. Then I added the mushrooms, some cayenne and Siracha and my fav Spike. I added parmesan to the polenta just after it was finished rather than later. Like another reviewer, I added balsamic at the very end to the kale mixture and then added all to the polenta so it could rest on top and the liquid could drain down to the polenta. Made for a dinner party and everyone loved it! Goes well with fried chicken.

