Rating: 4
Yum! This is a fabulous dish, and while it uses 3 pots and pans, the preparation isn't complicated. For those who are watching their fat intake, I prepared the dish using low-fat milk, and just a tsp. of olive oil in the whole meal (to saute the mushrooms), and did not stir butter or cheese into the finished polenta. Instead, I grated about 1 T. fresh parmesan directly over each serving of polenta after I had plated it, and before the vegetables went on top. I also doubled the mushrooms, and added a diced red pepper to the sauteing vegetables. I used dried thyme. The flavor was rich and bright. Really, a savory, wonderful meal.